%N A037661 Base 5 digits are, in order, the first n terms of the periodic sequence with initial period 3,1,0.
%H A037661 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,0,1,-5).
%F A037661 G.f.: x*(3+x) / ( (x-1)*(5*x-1)*(1+x+x^2) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 30 2015
%F A037661 a(n) = 5*a(n-1) + a(n-3) - 5*a(n-4). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Sep 05 2022
%F A037661 a(n) = floor(20*5^n/31). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 06 2026
%F A037661 E.g.f.: exp(-x/2)*(-31*exp(3*x/2) + 60*exp(11*x/2) - 29*cos(sqrt(3)*x/2) - 3*sqrt(3)*sin(sqrt(3)*x/2))/93. - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 06 2026
%t A037661 Module[{nn=30,c},c=PadRight[{},nn,{3,1,0}];Table[FromDigits[Take[c,n],5],{n,nn}]] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Feb 19 2013 *)
%K A037661 nonn,base,easy
%O A037661 1,1
%A A037661 _Clark Kimberling_
